  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Resident Technical Officer (Substation) (4 p.m to 1a.m)",
  "description": "<ol><li><strong>Minimum Diploma in Civil Engineering with at least 5 years' post tertiary experience in Singapore, of which 5 years must be supervision of Substation 66kV and above/ Data Center /Industrial / Factory projects as RTO</strong></li><li><strong>Registered Resident Technical Officer by IES</strong></li><li><strong>Basic knowledge of Architectural details and construction works on site</strong></li></ol><ul><li>Must be Registered with IES/ACES as a RE for RE C&S. RTO cert for RTO C&S.</li><li>Able to work odd hours (4am to 1pm)</li><li>Basic knowledge of Architectural details and construction works on site.</li><li> To supervise the project to ensure that the works are constructed in accordance to the project specifications, construction drawings, contract, Building Control Act and Regulations, authorities and client's requirements</li><li>Report to C&S QP, work closely with the regulatory authorities and contractors to provide supervision on site, resolve all site issues and ensure timely completion of the projects.</li><li>Carry out supervision of structural works by identifying any non-conformity of contractor's works on site.</li><li>Carry out regular site checks on Builder and ensure compliance on health and work safety in accordance with MOM.</li><li>Review Contractor's submissions, work method statements and work demonstrations.</li><li>Conduct regular site inspections and resolving site discrepancies to prevent delays.</li><li>Attend site, progress, variation and coordination meetings, highlighting foreseeable problems and recommending possible solutions.</li><li>Provide administrative control and maintaining proper records including site attendance, leave records, overtime records and inspections checklists</li></ul>",
